    "High diversity in immune-related responses is one possible pathogen resistance mechanism in plant communities 66, and therefore reduced diversity may have compromised modern Arabica cultivar immunity.",
    "The high level of conservation between the Arabica subgenomes and their diploid progenitors may have facilitated spontaneous interspecific hybridization events.",
    "This was the case for the Timor hybrid, a spontaneous Robusta × Arabica hybrid resistant to H. vastatrix 27.",
    "Our sample set included five descendants of the original Timor hybrid, obtained by backcrossing to Arabica.",
    "As expected, the hybridization affected subCC more profoundly, with much higher levels of nucleotide divergence apparent (F ST = 0.185) than in subEE (F ST = 0.0897), when comparing cultivars and hybrids."
